1. Using Git Diff

Q. Explain the purpose of git diff.
Ans. git diff: Displays the changes between the working directory and the staging area. It shows what has been changed but not yet staged for commit.

Q. How to use git diff to compare changes between commits, the working directory, and the staging area.
Ans. Using git diff to compare changes between commits, the working directory, and the staging area involves different commands depending on what you want to compare.

Assignment: Make some changes to a file and use git diff to view the differences.
Solution  :git diff
